@node Description "DESCRIPTION:"

DESCRIPTION
-----------

	This program will create a new file from any portion of
	an existing file.

@endnode

@node Requirements "REQUIREMENTS:"

REQUIREMENTS
------------

	An Amiga with at least as much Free RAM as the size of the
	Output File and about 10K to load and run RipFile.

@endnode

@node Usage "Usage"

USAGE
-----

	RipFile SourceFile SkipCount DestFile DestFileSize


		SourceFile:	Complete filename (Dir, Path, Filename) of the input file.
		SkipCount:	Number of bytes (from the beginning of the input file) to skip.
		DestFile:	Complete filename (Dir, Path, Filename) of the output file.
		DestFileSize:	Number of bytes to rip from the input file.   * can be used
					to specify to end of file.

@endnode

@node Output "Program Output:"

Program Output:

	Instructional message.

	Error Messages:

		File (input filename) not found.
		Error occurred during Memory allocation.
		Error occurred during File Examination.
		Error occurred during Open of input file.
		Error occurred during Open of output file.
	
@endnode

@node Compatibility "Compatibility"

COMPATIBILITY
-------------

This program was written and compiled on an A3000 w/Kickstarts 2.04/3.1
and WorkBenchs 2.1/3.1 with 8MB Fast 2MB Chip, 2MB ZorroII, Various Hard
drives and "Magic Kick ROMS".
 
Tested on:
A500	KickStarts	2.05/3.1
A600	KickStarts	2.06/3.1
A2000	KickStarts	2.05/3.1
A3000	KickStarts	Magic Kick ROMS

@endnode

@node History "History:"

HISTORY
-------

BUGS/UpGrades for RipFile:
 Version 1.0 - Corrupted memory if skip count was greater than 0.
 Version 1.1 - Fix skip count memory error.
 Version 1.2 - Reduced memory requirements to size of output file.

@endnode

